---
alwaysApply: true
---

While converting a VB6 form to .NET, treat channel / variant matrices as **`object[row, column]`** in C#.

Legacy VB uses **`variant(fieldIndex, recordIndex)`** (e.g. `Contract.dob`: `varExecutors(0, i)` = id / `ItemData`, `varExecutors(1, i)` = caption; loop `For i = 0 To UBound(variant, 2)`).

Map to C# by swapping subscripts: **`fieldIndex` → column, `recordIndex` → row.**

```csharp
int n = arr.GetLength(0);
for (int rowIndex = 0; rowIndex < n; rowIndex++)
{
    int id = Convert.ToInt32(arr[rowIndex, 0]);
    string name = Convert.ToString(arr[rowIndex, 1]);
}
```

So **`arr[rowIndex, 0]`** corresponds to **`variant(0, i)`** and **`arr[rowIndex, 1]`** to **`variant(1, i)`** when `rowIndex == i`.
